      • readLogHeader

        public static LogHeader readLogHeader​(ByteBuffer buffer,
                                      ReadableByteChannel channel,
                                      boolean strict,
                                      Path fileForAdditionalErrorInformationOrNull)
                               throws IOException
        Reads the header of a log. Data will be read from channel using supplied buffer as to allow more controlled allocation.
        Parameters:
        buffer - ByteBuffer to read into. Passed in to allow control over allocation.
        channel - ReadableByteChannel to read from, typically a channel over a file containing the data.
        strict - if true then will fail with IncompleteLogHeaderException on incomplete header, i.e. if there's not enough data in the channel to even read the header. If false then the return value will instead be null.
        fileForAdditionalErrorInformationOrNull - when in strict mode the exception can be amended with information about which file the channel represents, if any. Purely for better forensics ability.
        Returns:
        LogHeader containing the log header data from the channel.
        Throws:
        IOException - if unable to read from channel
        IncompleteLogHeaderException - if strict and not enough data could be read
